  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Civil Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<p>Be part of a <strong>leading main contractor</strong> with opportunities to contribute to <strong>roadworks, and LTA infrastructure projects</strong>. This role offers exposure to diverse and large-scale works, giving you the platform to sharpen your technical skills and accelerate your career.</p><p><strong>Why Join Us:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Exposure to <strong>landmark projects</strong>: infrastructure LTA works, roadworks</p></li><li><p>Clear pathways for <strong>career growth & development</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Competitive salary, benefits, and training support</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>What You'll Do:</strong><br /><strong>As a key member of the company's team, you'll play a vital role in ensuring the successful execution of their projects. Your responsibilities will include:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Analyzing Contract Documents: Dive deep into contract specifications, perform precise measurements, and prepare comprehensive Bills of Quantities.</p></li><li><p>Contract Administration: Assist in managing contracts by preparing progress claims and collaborating with company's Clients' representatives on claims and variations.</p></li><li><p>Tender Pricing: Request quotations, analyze prices, and prepare detailed bills of quantities to ensure competitive tender pricing.</p></li><li><p>Claims Verification: Review and verify subcontractor and supplier claims, preparing accurate payment certificates to maintain financial integrity.</p></li><li><p>Engaging in Meetings: Participate in site and progress claim meetings to ensure clear communication and project alignment.</p></li><li><p>Project Monitoring: After project completion, oversee the project during the defects liability period to uphold our commitment to quality.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Degree/Diploma in Quantity Surveying or equivalent qualifications</p></li><li><p>Preferably at least 2 years of relevant working experience in Civil Engineering</p></li><li><p>Good technical and contractual knowledge with high integrity and work ethic</p></li><li><p>An independent and effective team player, collaborating on multi-projects of various stages, ensuring deliverables within set time & expectations.</p></li></ul><p>How to Apply:<br />Interested candidates, please submit your updated resume by using Apply Now button<br />We regret to inform that only shortlisted candidates will be informed.<br /></p><p>Yip Seow Thung<br />Registration Number: R24121304<br />EA License No: 18C9027</p>",
